{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"G4 child-consistency audit (parent WS-EVAL-EXISTING vs this child 7402 + full sibling roster: 476f, 4569, c156). 7 cross-child interaction modes checked; 2 modes flagged (scope overlap + dependency/ordering gap on label-adjudication <-> gold_set ownership). The other 5 modes are clean.\n\nFINDING 1 — Scope overlap: gold_set label adjudication is claimed by BOTH 7402 and c156 with no stated partition.\n- criteria: 7402 AC3 (\"Ground-truth labels are adjudicated and recorded; seed labels marked provisional\"); c156 AC1/AC3 (each spec ships a non-empty gold_set; \"Datasets are balanced, corpus-tagged, and seeded from real observed cases where available\"); parent AC1 (\"non-empty gold_set\").\n- location: 7402 description \"adjudicate ground-truth labels (define labeler/consensus; seed labels provisional per the existing eval README convention)\" vs c156 spec authoring (`src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/*.eval.yaml` with gold_set).\n- evidence: In the established pattern the kappa-gating gold_set is the human-ADJUDICATED, provisional-SEED-labeled subset embedded INLINE in each spec file — src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/plan-review-finder.eval.yaml:179-189 (\"Frozen human-gold subset ... SEED labels — pending human adjudication\"); src/rebar/llm/eval_specs/README.plan-review.md:34-43 (\"Gold subset + human adjudication ... labels shipped here are a best-effort SEED pending human adjudication\"). 7402 AC3 (adjudicate + mark provisional) and c156 AC1/AC3 (ship non-empty gold_set with seeded labels) therefore describe the SAME artifact — the adjudicated/provisional gold labels — with no declared owner.\n- scenarios: c156 author writes inline gold_set seed labels per the README convention while 7402 author independently runs the adjudication/labeler-consensus step -> duplicated or divergent label sets; OR each assumes the other owns it and the gold_set ships unadjudicated.\n- impact: ambiguous ownership of the kappa-gating labels; risk of a divergent or unadjudicated gold_set, undermining the judge-alignment (kappa-over-gold_set) gate wired by 4569.\n- checklist_item: scope overlap\n- suggested_fix: Partition explicitly — e.g. 7402 owns the adjudication PROCESS + provisional labels and hands them to c156, which embeds the resulting gold_set per spec; or move the gold_set/label-adjudication AC entirely into one child and have the other reference it.\n\nFINDING 2 — Dependency/ordering gap: c156's gold_set deliverable depends on 7402's label adjudication, but no dep links them and the order is not enforced.\n- criteria: c156 AC1 (non-empty gold_set per spec) + AC4 (offline test asserts non-empty gold_set) depend on 7402 AC3 (adjudicated/provisional ground-truth labels).\n- location: dep graph — c156 depends_on 476f ONLY; 7402 depends_on 476f ONLY; no c156<->7402 link. 4569 depends_on both c156 and 7402, so they converge only at the wiring child.\n- evidence: 7402 description owns \"adjudicate ground-truth labels ... seed labels provisional per the existing eval README convention\"; README.plan-review.md:34-43 ties those adjudicated/seed labels directly to the gold_set that c156 must ship. With no ordering link, c156 can be executed/closed before 7402 produces the adjudicated labels.\n- scenarios: c156 ships specs with placeholder gold_set labels ahead of 7402's adjudication -> labels never reconciled, or rework when 7402's adjudicated labels land after c156 is done.\n- impact: silent ordering inversion between label production (7402) and gold_set consumption (c156); gold_set may ship un-adjudicated or require post-hoc rework.\n- checklist_item: dependency gap / ordering violation\n- suggested_fix: Either add c156 depends_on 7402 (adjudication before spec gold_set finalization), or explicitly scope seed-labels-in-spec to c156 and the formal adjudication to 7402 as a follow-on that REVISES the seed (matching the \"provisional pending adjudication\" convention), making the ordering explicit.\n\nClean modes: implicit shared state (fixture corpus + dataset schema from 476f surfaced via 7402->476f dep; solver consumed by 4569 via 4569->7402 dep — all explicit), conflicting assumptions (FakeRunner/FakeAgentRunner offline-no-token consistent with 4569's pinned offline discipline; provisional-seed labeling consistent with README convention), consumer impact (solver+stubs consumed by 4569, dep present), residual references (FakeRunner / eval README convention reference pre-existing infra; no dangling refs to removed/renamed siblings)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782580061274107001,"uuid":"844ba9a3-7cbf-4ee8-b33f-b30f968dda2b"}